channel.title: Papers with Code: Latest (unofficial)
channel.description: As a disclaimer, this is an unofficial feed and has no affiliation with Papers with Code.

item.title: Effect of prolonged use of Smartphones on neck and wrist muscle fatigue using surface EMG
item.description: Prolonged smartphone usage is prevalent among young adults in Lima, Peru, with potential implications for musculoskeletal health.

item.title: AlignBench: Benchmarking Chinese Alignment of Large Language Models
item.description: Alignment has become a critical step for instruction-tuned Large Language Models (LLMs) to become helpful assistants.

item.title: Controlgym: Large-Scale Safety-Critical Control Environments for Benchmarking Reinforcement Learning Algorithms
item.description: This project serves the learning for dynamics & control (L4DC) community, aiming to explore key questions: the convergence of RL algorithms in learning control policies; the stability and robustness issues of learning-based controllers; and the scalability of RL algorithms to high- and potentially infinite-dimensional systems.

item.title: $\mathbb{Z}_2\times \mathbb{Z}_2$ Equivariant Quantum Neural Networks: Benchmarking against Classical Neural Networks
item.description: Our results show that the $\mathbb{Z}_2\times \mathbb{Z}_2$ EQNN and the QNN provide superior performance for smaller parameter sets and modest training data samples.

item.title: Exploiting Diffusion Prior for Generalizable Pixel-Level Semantic Prediction
item.description: Contents generated by recent advanced Text-to-Image (T2I) diffusion models are sometimes too imaginative for existing off-the-shelf property semantic predictors to estimate due to the immitigable domain gap.

item.title: Towards Assessing and Benchmarking Risk-Return Tradeoff of Off-Policy Evaluation
item.description: This efficient estimator is characterized by its capability to form the most advantageous policy portfolios, maximizing returns while minimizing risks during online deployment, a nuance that existing metrics typically overlook.

item.title: ElasticDiffusion: Training-free Arbitrary Size Image Generation
item.description: We propose ElasticDiffusion, a novel training-free decoding method that enables pretrained text-to-image diffusion models to generate images with various sizes.

item.title: Language Model Agents Suffer from Compositional Generalization in Web Automation
item.description: We show that while existing prompted LMAs (gpt-3. 5-turbo or gpt-4) achieve 94. 0% average success rate on base tasks, their performance degrades to 24. 9% success rate on compositional tasks.

item.title: Routing-Guided Learned Product Quantization for Graph-Based Approximate Nearest Neighbor Search
item.description: It suffers from the large-scale $\mathcal{X}$ because a PG with full vectors is too large to fit into the memory, e. g., a billion-scale $\mathcal{X}$ in 128 dimensions would consume nearly 600 GB memory.

item.title: Compact3D: Compressing Gaussian Splat Radiance Field Models with Vector Quantization
item.description: 3D Gaussian Splatting is a new method for modeling and rendering 3D radiance fields that achieves much faster learning and rendering time compared to SOTA NeRF methods.

item.title: What Do Llamas Really Think? Revealing Preference Biases in Language Model Representations
item.description: We propose a logistic Bradley-Terry probe which predicts word pair preferences of LLMs from the words' hidden vectors.

item.title: MotionEditor: Editing Video Motion via Content-Aware Diffusion
item.description: This mechanism enables the editing branch to query the key and value from the reconstruction branch in a decoupled manner, making the editing branch retain the original background and protagonist appearance.

item.title: LLVMs4Protest: Harnessing the Power of Large Language and Vision Models for Deciphering Protests in the News
item.description: First, the longformer model was fine-tuned using the Dynamic of Collective Action (DoCA) Corpus.

item.title: LMRL Gym: Benchmarks for Multi-Turn Reinforcement Learning with Language Models
item.description: Developing such algorithms requires tasks that can gauge progress on algorithm design, provide accessible and reproducible evaluations for multi-turn interactions, and cover a range of task properties and challenges in improving reinforcement learning algorithms.

item.title: Accurate Segmentation of Optic Disc And Cup from Multiple Pseudo-labels by Noise-Aware Learning
item.description: The training framework of the MPNN is constructed by a teacher-student architecture to learn segmentation from clean pixels and noisy pixels.

item.title: FRC-GIF: Frame Ranking-based Personalized Artistic Media Generation Method for Resource Constrained Devices
item.description: Generating video highlights in the form of animated graphics interchange formats (GIFs) has significantly simplified the process of video browsing.

item.title: On the convergence of adaptive first order methods: proximal gradient and alternating minimization algorithms
item.description: Building upon recent works on linesearch-free adaptive proximal gradient methods, this paper proposes AdaPG$^{\pi, r}$, a framework that unifies and extends existing results by providing larger stepsize policies and improved lower bounds.

item.title: CAST: Cross-Attention in Space and Time for Video Action Recognition
item.description: In this work, we propose a novel two-stream architecture, called Cross-Attention in Space and Time (CAST), that achieves a balanced spatio-temporal understanding of videos using only RGB input.

item.title: A Comparison Between Invariant and Equivariant Classical and Quantum Graph Neural Networks
item.description: In this paper, we perform a fair and comprehensive comparison between classical graph neural networks (GNNs) and equivariant graph neural networks (EGNNs) and their quantum counterparts: quantum graph neural networks (QGNNs) and equivariant quantum graph neural networks (EQGNN).

item.title: CritiqueLLM: Scaling LLM-as-Critic for Effective and Explainable Evaluation of Large Language Model Generation
item.description: Since the natural language processing (NLP) community started to make large language models (LLMs), such as GPT-4, act as a critic to evaluate the quality of generated texts, most of them only train a critique generation model of a specific scale on specific datasets.

item.title: mPLUG-PaperOwl: Scientific Diagram Analysis with the Multimodal Large Language Model
item.description: In this work, towards a more versatile copilot for academic paper writing, we mainly focus on strengthening the multi-modal diagram analysis ability of Multimodal LLMs.

item.title: HOLD: Category-agnostic 3D Reconstruction of Interacting Hands and Objects from Video
item.description: Since humans interact with diverse objects every day, the holistic 3D capture of these interactions is important to understand and model human behaviour.

item.title: Perturbation-based Analysis of Compositional Data
item.description: Existing statistical methods for compositional data analysis are inadequate for many modern applications for two reasons.

item.title: Steering Deep Feature Learning with Backward Aligned Feature Updates
item.description: Deep learning succeeds by doing hierarchical feature learning, yet tuning Hyper-Parameters (HP) such as initialization scales, learning rates etc., only give indirect control over this behavior.

item.title: CoRec: An Easy Approach for Coordination Recognition
item.description: In this paper, we observe and address the challenges of the coordination recognition task.

item.title: InstructSeq: Unifying Vision Tasks with Instruction-conditioned Multi-modal Sequence Generation
item.description: In this work, we introduce InstructSeq, an instruction-conditioned multi-modal modeling framework that unifies diverse vision tasks through flexible natural language control and handling of both visual and textual data.

item.title: Optimizing ZX-Diagrams with Deep Reinforcement Learning
item.description: ZX-diagrams are a powerful graphical language for the description of quantum processes with applications in fundamental quantum mechanics, quantum circuit optimization, tensor network simulation, and many more.

item.title: LL3DA: Visual Interactive Instruction Tuning for Omni-3D Understanding, Reasoning, and Planning
item.description: However, developing LMMs that can comprehend, reason, and plan in complex and diverse 3D environments remains a challenging topic, especially considering the demand for understanding permutation-invariant point cloud 3D representations of the 3D scene.

item.title: SCOPE-RL: A Python Library for Offline Reinforcement Learning and Off-Policy Evaluation
item.description: This paper introduces SCOPE-RL, a comprehensive open-source Python software designed for offline reinforcement learning (offline RL), off-policy evaluation (OPE), and selection (OPS).

item.title: Hubness Reduction Improves Sentence-BERT Semantic Spaces
item.description: We find that when hubness is high, we can reduce error rate and hubness using hubness reduction methods.

item.title: Detection of tonic-clonic seizures in children with epilepsy
item.description: Epilepsy, a neurological condition characterized by recurrent, unprovoked seizures, profoundly impacts the lives of approximately 50 million individuals worldwide.

item.title: TaskBench: Benchmarking Large Language Models for Task Automation
item.description: To this end, we introduce TaskBench to evaluate the capability of LLMs in task automation.

item.title: Is Underwater Image Enhancement All Object Detectors Need?
item.description: Coupled with 7 object detection models retrained using raw underwater images, we employ these 133 models to comprehensively analyze the effect of underwater image enhancement on underwater object detection.

item.title: TLDR: Text Based Last-layer Retraining for Debiasing Image Classifiers
item.description: Recently, Last Layer Retraining (LLR) with group-balanced datasets is known to be efficient in mitigating the spurious correlation of classifiers.

item.title: X-InstructBLIP: A Framework for aligning X-Modal instruction-aware representations to LLMs and Emergent Cross-modal Reasoning
item.description: Vision-language pre-training and instruction tuning have demonstrated general-purpose capabilities in 2D visual reasoning tasks by aligning visual encoders with state-of-the-art large language models (LLMs).

item.title: TCP:Textual-based Class-aware Prompt tuning for Visual-Language Model
item.description: However, those textual tokens have a limited generalization ability regarding unseen domains, as they cannot dynamically adjust to the distribution of testing classes.

item.title: ArcMMLU: A Library and Information Science Benchmark for Large Language Models
item.description: In response to this need, this paper introduces ArcMMLU, a specialized benchmark tailored for the Library & Information Science (LIS) domain in Chinese.

item.title: A data-science pipeline to enable the Interpretability of Many-Objective Feature Selection
item.description: The methodology supports the data scientist in the selection of an optimal feature subset by providing her with high-level information at three different levels: objectives, solutions, and individual features.

item.title: Dichotomy of Early and Late Phase Implicit Biases Can Provably Induce Grokking
item.description: Recent work by Power et al. (2022) highlighted a surprising "grokking" phenomenon in learning arithmetic tasks: a neural net first "memorizes" the training set, resulting in perfect training accuracy but near-random test accuracy, and after training for sufficiently longer, it suddenly transitions to perfect test accuracy.

item.title: TransCORALNet: A Two-Stream Transformer CORAL Networks for Supply Chain Credit Assessment Cold Start
item.description: Thanks to the domain adaptation capability of the proposed model, the domain shift between the source and target domain is minimized.

item.title: Exploring the hierarchical structure of human plans via program generation
item.description: We find that humans are sensitive to both metrics, but that both accounts fail to predict a qualitative feature of human-created programs, namely that people prefer programs with reuse over and above the predictions of MDL.

item.title: Prompt-Based Exemplar Super-Compression and Regeneration for Class-Incremental Learning
item.description: Replay-based methods in class-incremental learning (CIL) have attained remarkable success, as replaying the exemplars of old classes can significantly mitigate catastrophic forgetting.

item.title: Evaluating the Impact of Flaky Simulators on Testing Autonomous Driving Systems
item.description: Our empirical results, obtained from two widely-used open-source ADS simulators and five diverse ADS test setups, show that test flakiness in ADS is a common occurrence and can significantly impact the test results obtained by randomized algorithms.

item.title: MLLMs-Augmented Visual-Language Representation Learning
item.description: Visual-language pre-training (VLP) have achieved remarkable success in multi-modal tasks, largely attributed to the availability of large-scale image-text datasets.

item.title: Learning Robust Precipitation Forecaster by Temporal Frame Interpolation
item.description: Recent advancements in deep learning have propelled the field of weather prediction models to new heights.

item.title: MaXTron: Mask Transformer with Trajectory Attention for Video Panoptic Segmentation
item.description: To alleviate the issue, we propose to adapt the trajectory attention for both the dense pixel features and object queries, aiming to improve the short-term and long-term tracking results, respectively.

item.title: Solving the Team Orienteering Problem with Transformers
item.description: This problem is usually modeled as a Combinatorial Optimization problem named as Team Orienteering Problem.

item.title: TIDE: Test Time Few Shot Object Detection
item.description: Few-shot object detection (FSOD) aims to extract semantic knowledge from limited object instances of novel categories within a target domain.

item.title: CAT-DM: Controllable Accelerated Virtual Try-on with Diffusion Model
item.description: Image-based virtual try-on enables users to virtually try on different garments by altering original clothes in their photographs.

item.title: FFT: Towards Harmlessness Evaluation and Analysis for LLMs with Factuality, Fairness, Toxicity
item.description: The widespread of generative artificial intelligence has heightened concerns about the potential harms posed by AI-generated texts, primarily stemming from factoid, unfair, and toxic content.
